The evidence with the title 'CEO pay: redefining sky-high - aug. 30, 2005 ' says Aug 30, 2005  ... In 2004, the ratio of average ceo pay to the average pay of a production (i.e., non-management) worker was 431-to-1, up from 301-to-1 in 2003,  ... Had the minimum wage risen as fast as ceo compensation since 1990, the researchers calculated, it would now be $23.03 an hour instead of just $5.15. 
